      • createConflictCounterExampleProxy

        public ConflictCounterExampleProxy createConflictCounterExampleProxy(String name,
                                                                     ProductDESProxy des,
                                                                     List<? extends EventProxy> events,
                                                                     ConflictKind kind)
        Description copied from interface: ProductDESProxyFactory
        Creates a new conflict counterexample using default values. This method provides a simple interface to create a counterexample for a deterministic product DES. It creates a counterexample with a null file location, with no comment, with a set of automata equal to that of the product DES, and without any state information in the trace steps.
        Specified by:
        createConflictCounterExampleProxy in interface ProductDESProxyFactory
        Parameters:
        name - The name to be given to the new counterexample.
        des - The product DES for which the new counterexample is generated.
        events - The list of events constituting the new counterexample, or null if empty.
        kind - The type of this conflict counterexample, one of ConflictKind.CONFLICT, ConflictKind.DEADLOCK, or ConflictKind.LIVELOCK.

                                                                 List<? extends EventProxy> events)
        Description copied from interface: ProductDESProxyFactory
        Creates a new safety counterexample using default values. This method provides a simple interface to create a controllability counterexample for a deterministic product DES. It creates a trace with a null file location, with the name of the product DES concatenated with "uncontrollable", with a set of automata equal to that of the product DES, and without any state information in the trace steps.
